      "content": "We can attribute the initial event to a \"configuration drift\" within our cloud infrastructure, which is a common, complex issue in large-scale deployments. This sounds highly technical and sophisticated, implying an internal process failure rather than a simple human error. We can then pivot immediately to how our automated compliance checks caught the drift and corrected it instantly, showcasing our robust, self-healing architecture.",
